<h2><a href="http://thinkvitamin.com/business/talking-strategy/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Talking Strategy">Talking Strategy</a></h2>
<p class="postDetails">By <a href="http://thinkvitamin.com/author/alexisbrion/" title="Posts by Alexis Brion">Alexis Brion</a> | 15 December 2010 | Category: <a href="http://thinkvitamin.com/category/business/" title="View all posts in Business" rel="category tag">Business</a></p>
<p>Talking about your client&#8217;s strategy with your client is a great way to kick off a project. You will get valuable information to start the design process and stakeholders will feel they are involved in the project right from the beginning.</p>
<p>A meeting to talk about the strategy to follow for a particular product should include some brainstorming along with an idea-sharing exercise to better understand the company and to learn what the stakeholders know about users&#8217; needs; this is necessary to make a match between user experience and business value.</p>
 
</div>
</article> <article class="standardPost typeLink">
<div class="articleIcons">
<span>Link</span>
</div>
<div class="postPreview">
<h2><a href="http://thinkvitamin.com/asides/requiring-email-and-passwords-for-new-accounts-on-instapaper/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Requiring email and passwords for new accounts on Instapaper">Requiring email and passwords for new accounts on Instapaper</a></h2>
